The paper deals with MDS array codes, which are commonly used in storage systems, and focuses on the problem of the "rebuilding ratio" in the case of erasures. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS), as well as distributed computing (cs.DC), scientific computing (cs.SI), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also mentions efficient encoding and decoding algorithms, which further supports the relevance of cs.IT and cs.DS.
